{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dcced370-fc43-4615-af58-df12d3cf89fe","content":"\n\nHere are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\nAuth options: `None`, `Individual` (Identity/JWT), `IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `MultiOrg`, `Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express** — Use packages like `passport`, `jsonwebtoken`, or `express-oauth2-jwt-bearer` for JWT/OAuth2.\n\n**Python / FastAPI** — Built-in `OAuth2PasswordBearer` or libraries like `python-jose` for JWT.\n\n---\n\n**Common auth approaches across stacks:**\n- **JWT Bearer tokens** — stateless, widely used for APIs\n- **OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect** — delegate to identity providers (Azure AD, Auth0, Okta)\n- **API Keys** — simple but less secure\n- **Cookie-based** — typical for server-rendered apps, less common for APIs\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project? If so, let me know your preferred language/framework and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4bd0effb-6e52-414a-b99c-379d28584af9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common options.","outputTokens":333},"id":"b7a2a9b8-4190-4b60-9ecd-9551d66fb5cb","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:43:54.215Z","parentId":"c7dfd7e7-5692-4cd6-8595-91fcb917fac3"}
